<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 03 at 11:28PM EDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Cherokee and central Clay Counties through 1215 AM EDT...
At 1127 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Andrews, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Andrews, Murphy, Nantahala Lake, Topton, Tusquitee and Marble.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
